    "Additional evaluations on new models and trigger types are in Sections J and I.",
    "An ablation study (Section D) confirms SHIP's robustness across hyper-parameter and fine-tuning variations.",
    "MMLU assessments (Section K) show hijacking and fine-tuning do not degrade general language abilities.",
    "Finally, we demonstrate trigger transferability to unseen system prompts in Section M.",
    "We introduced SHIP, a hidden exploit to bypass system prompts, implanted by the base LLM provider that persists through fine-tuning and can be activated by a malicious end user."
